name: bendansie
bio:
Greetings all! 3D artist with over 10 years professional experience working in Australia with a passion for 3d printing and how it can bridge digital and traditional / physical art forms. Largely a Blender / Zbrush user. Working in jewellery, medals, replica work, mild prototyping and of course character sculpture.

Available for commissions!

name: emmett
bio: I'm an aerospace engineer working at Google on [<model-viewer\>](https://googlewebcomponents.github.io/model-viewer/). I previously worked at a 3D video [startup](https://www.omnivor.io/) and at Microsoft on [3MF](http://www.3mf.io) and [3D Builder and 3D print drivers](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/hardware/bg183398). 3D design is my hobby, and that's how I got started. All my designs are available for free under a CC-BY-SA license, so all I ask is attribution. My doctorate is in control theory, and if you're interested, you can find all my research publications and dissertation [here](http://www.aa.washington.edu/research/ndcl/publications.html).

name: mz4250
bio: Hello guys. I'm a massive Dungeons & Dragons fan who loves to share his fanart here so fellow gamers can customize their games as much as I do. Years ago WOTC requested I don't post their intellectual property here but were ok with posting my works on Shapeways, so you can find the rest of my works here: https://www.shapeways.com/designer/mz4250 You gotta log in first before you see the "download product" button on each mini's page. Thankfully its all free. Regardless of this, as you can see I still have hundreds of models here ready for your download and enjoyment. My Patreon is here if you'd like to support my efforts. https://www.patreon.com/mz4250 I offer my patrons access to a Google Drive with all my files, a Commercial Friendly Drive if they want to sell prints of my models, a request board, and much more. If you'd like to support my efforts as I make free models for the world you're welcome to sign up :-) Enjoy and happy printing! Become a Patron! Links to all my stl sources and other media: https://linktr.ee/mz4250
